    ├── AnimationTrack
    └── AnimationTimeline
If SceneNodes can be animated (transform animations, visibility, skeletal animations).
SceneNode animations typically deal with how the scene nodes themselves are animated.
This includes:
    1.  Transform Animations:
        Moving, rotating, or scaling the entire object or node.
    2.  Visibility Animations:
        Making an object appear/disappear or fade in/out.
    3.  Skeletal Animations:
        Animating bones in a model, typically for characters (more complex).


